                        "html_value":  "",
                        "value":  [
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "84689117-2f01-41df-9292-6f72e1f29a82",
                                          "name":  "The Planet Earth",
                                          "desc":  "The Planet Earth",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "9ba0eaa0-b7fd-46f4-aacf-862cbbfd50bd",
                                          "name":  "Earth: A \"Living\" Planet",
                                          "desc":  "<p>When discussing maps, it is essential to consider geological time, as continents have not always existed in their present form. Besides the continental landmasses, we must also account for tectonic plate movements, which play a major role in the formation and transformation of visible land structures</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "67a4d43b-5d13-409e-9937-d255a49da844",
                                          "name":  "Continent: Antarctica",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, Antarctica is displayed at the southernmost part of the planet, with the regions of South America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Africa, and Australia also visible</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "ac8263df-f6bc-4c86-802d-fe7cde244fde",
                                          "name":  "Continent: Africa",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, the Africa is higlighted, with the regions of South America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Antarctida, Europe and Asia also visible</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "4272d70c-7ebf-475a-bd72-0f7430dcdb0d",
                                          "name":  "Bantu Expansion",
                                          "desc":  "Bantu Expansion",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "0a108a48-b9f6-4c5a-afe2-4c289c21aadb",
                                          "name":  "Great Zimbabwe",
                                          "desc":  "Great Zimbabwe",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "66e740ed-ced9-4e7d-8d2f-b351df559d95",
                                          "name":  "Continent: Asia",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, Asia is highlighted, with the regions of North America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Africa, Europe, and Australia also represented</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "b4d6b6bb-fcc2-4ea1-b0e1-80d980539ee1",
                                          "name":  "Where is the center?",
                                          "desc":  "Where is the center?",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "18b9d913-7357-4852-a5e0-db6a4d0cf1c5",
                                          "name":  "Subcontinent: South America",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, the South American (<i>Abya Yala</i>) subcontinent is highlighted, with Central America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), North America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Africa, Europe, and Antarctica also represented</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "ea01ab6c-26af-4c7a-ba06-5c1731c83d4d",
                                          "name":  "America: Inca (Tawantinsuyu)",
                                          "desc":  "America: Inca (Tawantinsuyu)",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "f928ce12-1718-4750-ba1d-70d72c20f2e1",
                                          "name":  "America: Minas Gerais (BR)",
                                          "desc":  "<p>The image in this section shows the current territory of Minas Gerais, in Brazil (<i>Pindorama</i>). The state has had this shape since approximately the end of the colonial period. The word \"Pindorama\", meaning \"Land of the Palm Trees\", was the name used to refer to the region before the arrival of colonizers</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "79179a04-9d77-414c-93ec-34c8722ee03e",
                                          "name":  "Subcontinent: North America",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, the subcontinent North America (<i>Abya Yala</i>) is highlighted, while the regions of South America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Asia, and Europe are also represented. It is important to note that Central America (<i>Abya Yala</i>) and North America (<i>Abya Yala</i>) are presented as a unified subcontinent; however, some studies treat them separately</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "8862783b-6213-40e7-9368-c3a048e265b5",
                                          "name":  "America: Mesoamerica (The Beginning)",
                                          "desc":  "America: Mesoamerica (The Beginning)",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "baba4f82-167b-4030-befb-bb6ae1144ac7",
                                          "name":  "America: Mesoamerica (Different Frontiers)",
                                          "desc":  "America: Mesoamerica (Different Frontiers)",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "5c90611b-96d4-4f83-b4ee-bd1b7f2e15f9",
                                          "name":  "Continent: Europe",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, the European continent is highlighted, while the regions of the Americas (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Africa, and Asia are also represented</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "841a7034-0902-42dd-8a24-e52bb0a9ad58",
                                          "name":  "Europe: Visigoths",
                                          "desc":  "<p>The exact origin of the Goths is uncertain, as they left no early written records. Some scholars suggest they may have originated in what is now Poland. There is also debate on whether the Goths constituted a distinct ethnic group; some researchers believe they may have been a confederation of various tribes</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "e8ac213e-b7b7-45a5-b911-902e37f8229c",
                                          "name":  "Europe: Banu Qasi",
                                          "desc":  "Europe: Banu Qasi",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "5adec388-3fce-4543-bd47-66dfeddb81ad",
                                          "name":  "Europe: Kingdom of León",
                                          "desc":  "Europe: Kingdom of León",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "94340649-971b-45bb-97d9-715b29bf399b",
                                          "name":  "Continent: Oceania",
                                          "desc":  "<p>In this map, the continent of Oceania is highlighted, while the regions of North America (<i>Abya Yala</i>), Antarctica, and Asia are also represented</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "7c7a3259-88e0-47b8-920c-9a5baacdb212",
                                          "name":  "The Size of the Earth",
                                          "desc":  "<p>The understanding that the Earth is spherical dates back thousands of years. The ancient Greeks reached this conclusion by observing how ship masts disappeared over the horizon and by noting the Earth’s shadow cast on the Moon during lunar eclipses. However, these observations did not provide a precise measurement of the Earth’s roundness. The first confirmed measurement was made around <htdate0> by Eratosthenes. On the summer solstice, he observed that in the city of Syene, the Sun’s rays reached straight to the bottom of a well, while in Alexandria, a pole cast a shadow pointing south. By knowing the properties of circles and the distance between Alexandria and Syene, Eratosthenes calculated the Earth’s circumference to be around 40,000 kilometers</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "53089395-6d49-4ea6-a138-e12b8e95a672",
                                          "name":  "Our Coordinates",
                                          "desc":  "Our Coordinates",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "23107400-ac34-4e64-855a-c1832fcc0b83",
                                          "name":  "The Myth of a Flat Earth",
                                          "desc":  "The Myth of a Flat Earth",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "1e6500ab-f416-449a-a175-3e13b7c269a0",
                                          "name":  "Map Projections",
                                          "desc":  "Map Projections",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "6f0135ff-cf7a-4025-84e5-da56ff0706d8",
                                          "name":  "Human Migration",
                                          "desc":  "Human Migration",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "405fc812-428d-4e0a-a6a4-c5627a2e7f46",
                                          "name":  "Cradle of Civilization",
                                          "desc":  "Cradle of Civilization",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "4b0bab6f-92ae-4ab9-aca6-b1626971b861",
                                          "name":  "Sumerians",
                                          "desc":  "Sumerians",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "e9687d71-a385-4c70-bf8e-e65c5962a928",
                                          "name":  "The Ancient Babylonian World Map",
                                          "desc":  "<p>Our understanding of the world has evolved over time. In antiquity, people represented the \"world\" as their immediate surroundings, rather than as the planet Earth as we know it today. The image in this section shows the world as envisioned by the Babylonians. In the next section, we project this map onto a modern world map to facilitate comparison</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      },
                                      {
                                          "family_id":  "",
                                          "person_id":  "",
                                          "id":  "98e6cd73-92bc-4d64-be97-9fda8bc85103",
                                          "name":  "Comparing Worlds",
                                          "desc":  "<p>To ilustrate the difference between Babilon vision of ancient world and in the past and our actual compreension, we followed Dr. Irving Finkel's analisis. We use the map of the section <i>Maps of Ancient World: Babilonia</i>, we rotate it and we put on top of our current understanding of world, as it is shwn in this section. It is possible to observe that Babilonian conception of the world did not include nearest regions, like India</p>",
                                          "date_time":  null
                                      }
                                  ],
                        "date_time":  null
                    }
                ],
    "date_time":  null
}
